rComments: Reza's class was probably the most enjoyable class I've taken. He is very passionate about architecture. What I love about Reza is that he has is own style of design, but he values other students' design styles. He is super helpful and approachable as well, and is always ready with ideas to push your design forward.

Reza is absolutely phenomenal, he's very approachable and helpful. I took this course during the summer and Im glad I had Reza as my prof because summer school is stressful. Reza was always available in class, out of class, thru email. His feedback and even criticism is always constructive. You will learn a lot from Reza, he is amazing!

The nicest prof I've ever had! Very patient with each student and took good amount of time to give suggestions and feedbacks. He carried markers and pens around and drew good conceptual drawings to help you gather ideas. Had good knowledge about architecture and was willing to share them rather than showed off during reviews.

Reza is probably the best prof I've had at Daniels. Gives solid feedback and is very down to earth and understanding. Likes more artistic work and the class itself is somewhat heavy but he respects students time extremely well.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]
